buy or sell the stock. You can also choose to share your buy on your social media feeds like Facebook, Twitter and LinkedIn. When youre done, click on Confirm. And there you go, you have just bought a stock!\n\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-2.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-259\" alt=\"image (2)\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-2-576x1024.png\" width=\"363\" height=\"645\" /></a>\n\n4.Similarly, when you want to sell a stock, you can access it through your positions by clicking the middle button and tapping on the <strong></strong> button. Then, repeat steps 2 and 3.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nBuying and selling a stock isn\'t all that hard once you get the hang of it. Of course, we strongly advise you to do prior research and read up on the actual market before buying or selling a stock. After all, all our data is reflective of the real world and stock market, so why not get more practice to prepare yourself for the real thing? ;)\n\nAnother important function of the application is the <strong>Trade History</strong>.\n\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-260\" alt=\"image\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-576x1024.png\" width=\"346\" height=\"614\" /></a>\n\nThis screen shows the detailed trade history for a position. You can view the quantity bought or sold, the date and the average price paid after the transaction.\n\n<strong>Realized P&amp;L</strong> is profit or loss banked into your virtual cash after the transaction.\n\n<strong>Unrealised P&amp;L</strong> is the floating profit or loss due to curret market price of the underlying stocks.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nUsing these information, you will be able to buy and sell a stock on TradeHero easily. Get started! sSt\n\n&nbsp;','Tutorial Part Two: Buy and Sell','','inherit','closed','open','','256-revision-11','','','2013-06-20 11:05:42','2013-06-20 03:05:42','',256,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/256-revision-11',0,'revision','',0),(8,2,'2013-05-03 04:43:23','2013-05-03 04:43:23','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://thvm-prod3.cloudapp.net/wordpress/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision','','','2013-05-03 04:43:23','2013-05-03 04:43:23','',2,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/2013/05/2-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(9,2,'2013-05-10 06:18:47','2013-05-10 06:18:47','','Press','','publish','open','open','','press','','','2013-06-13 17:38:45','2013-06-13 09:38:45','',0,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/?page_id=9',2,'page','',0),(10,2,'2013-05-10 06:18:24','2013-05-10 06:18:24','','Press','','inherit','open','open','','9-revision','','','2013-05-10 06:18:24','2013-05-10 06:18:24','',9,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/2013/05/9-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(130,4,'2013-06-13 18:34:46','2013-06-13 10:34:46','<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/blog3.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-178\" alt=\"blog3\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/blog3.png\" width=\"750\" height=\"250\" /></a>TradeHero has bee