 by the Hero over a weekly or monthly period.\r\n\r\nActive heroes are users you are currently following and paying for. Inactive heroes are users that you have stopped paying for.\r\n<h2><strong>6. Leaderboards</strong></h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/Leaderboatd.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-231\" alt=\"Leaderboatd\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/Leaderboatd.png\" width=\"328\" height=\"552\" /></a>\r\n\r\nLeaderboards rank the performance of individual users worldwide, make more trades and fight to reach the top of the leaderboard to gain followers!\r\n\r\nTo expand your options, you can tap on the names of the users. You can also view the users previous closed positions to find out how he reached his current profit level, but to view the users current open positions and receive push notifications when the user makes trades and comments,you will have to tap Follow User and subscribe to him.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe have just introduced the basic features of TradeHero and what we have to offer. Do look out for our next few tips and tutorials where we will explain more on how to<strong> Buy and Sell shares</strong>, as well as <strong>How to Earn Real Money</strong> using our application. Stay tuned!','Tutorial Part One: Introduction','','inherit','closed','open','','227-revision-18','','','2013-06-19 16:12:28','2013-06-19 08:12:28','',227,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/227-revision-18',0,'revision','',0),(256,4,'2013-07-01 16:36:17','2013-07-01 08:36:17','<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/tut3.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-268\" alt=\"tut3\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/tut3.png\" width=\"750\" height=\"250\" /></a>\r\n\r\nIn this tutorial, we will be showing you a step-by-step process on how to Buy and Sell a stock. Although it may seem simple given that the procedures are easy, it takes more than just steps in the trading world. In order to maximise your experience,we suggest looking beyond this tutorial after you grasp a basic understanding of the application.\r\n<h2><strong>How to Buy/Sell a stock using TradeHero:</strong></h2>\r\nTrade Price is set to the market ask price when buying, and the bid price when selling. This is to simulate Market Order type transactions. For some stocks, we don\'t have ask and bid data. For such stocks, we use the last traded price of the stock. One thing to note: Trade Quantity is limited to 20% of Average Daily Volume or Current Day Volume, whichever is higher.<!--more-->\r\n\r\n1. In the buy/sell screen, select a name of the stock. Use the search engine to search for stocks the supported exchanges. You can search by company or symbol name. Trending stocks simply means the stocks that other TradeHero users are buying and selling.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/buysell.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-257\" alt=\"buysell\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/buysell.png\" width=\"354\" height=\"551\" /></a>\r\n\r\n2. Use the charts and information provided on the screen to view market data to help you in your decision on whether to buy or sell a stock. (<em>These information will not be enough, its just a guide. You will definitely need more information than that.</em>) Then, use the slider to choose the quantity of stocks that you want to buy. Alternatively, you can use the prefixed amounts found below the slider.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/APPSTORE3_640x1136_2.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-258\" alt=\"APPSTORE3_640x1136_2\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/APPSTORE3_640x1136_2.png\" width=\"360\" height=\"619\" /></a>\r\n\r\n3.After clicking the Buy button, you can choose to post comments for reasons to buy or sell the stock. You can also choose to share your buy on your social media feeds like Facebook, Twitter and LinkedIn. When youre done, click on Confirm. And there you go, you have just bought yourself a stock!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-2.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-259\" alt=\"image (2)\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-2-576x1024.png\" width=\"363\" height=\"645\" /></a>\r\n\r\n4.Similarly, when you want to sell a stock, you can access it through your positions by clicking the middle button and tapping on the <strong></strong> button. Then, repeat steps 2 and 3.\r\n\r\nBuying and selling a stock isn\'t all that hard once you get the hang of it. Of course, we strongly advise you to do prior research and read up on the actual stock market before buying or selling a stock. After all, all our data is reflective of the real world and stock market, so why not get more practice to prepare yourself for the real thing?\r\n\r\nAnother important function of the application is the <strong>Trade History</strong>.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-260\" alt=\"image\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-576x1024.png\" width=\"346\" height=\"614\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThis screen shows the detailed trade history for a position. You can view the quantity bought or sold, the date and the average price paid after the transaction.\r\n\r\n<strong>Realized P&amp;L</strong> is profit or loss banked into your virtual cash after the transaction.\r\n\r\n<strong>Unrealised P&amp;L</strong> is the floating profit or loss due to curret market price of the underlying stocks.\r\n\r\nFind out more at our <a href=\"http://www.tradehero.mobi/FAQ\">FAQ</a> page!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOh yes, not forgetting one of the most significant features of TradeHero: <strong>Stock Alerts.</strong>\r\n\r\nStock alerts are designed specially for users to help receive information and keep up to date on stock price movements so that users like you are able to take necessary action at the best possible time. You will receive instant notifications whenever a stock hits a target price or moves by a selected percentage. Such prime information at such a low price, it is definitely a feature not to missed if you want to keep up with the stock market!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nUsing these information, you will be able to buy and sell a stock on TradeHero easily. Get started! Stay tuned for more tips from TradeHero. Have a look at Part One of the tutorials <a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/tutorial-part-one-introduction\">here</a>, or visit our Facebook at <a href=\"http://facebook.com/TradeHero\">TradeHero</a>!! Til then!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Tutorial Part Two: Buy and Sell','','publish','closed','open','','tutorial-part-two-buy-and-sell','','','2013-07-05 12:09:01','2013-07-05 04:09:01','',0,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/?p=256',0,'post','',0),(257,4,'2013-06-19 17:32:38','2013-06-19 09:32:38','','buysell','','inherit','closed','open','','buysell','','','2013-06-19 17:32:38','2013-06-19 09:32:38','',256,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/buysell.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(258,4,'2013-06-19 17:34:56','2013-06-19 09:34:56','','APPSTORE3_640x1136_2','','inherit','closed','open','','appstore3_640x1136_2','','','2013-06-19 17:34:56','2013-06-19 09:34:56','',256,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/APPSTORE3_640x1136_2.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(259,4,'2013-06-19 17:35:51','2013-06-19 09:35:51','','image (2)','','inherit','closed','open','','image-2','','','2013-06-19 17:35:51','2013-06-19 09:35:51','',256,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-2.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(260,4,'2013-06-19 17:41:32','2013-06-19 09:41:32','','image','','inherit','closed','open','','image','','','2013-06-19 17:41:32','2013-06-19 09:41:32','',256,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(261,4,'2013-06-19 17:48:17','2013-06-19 09:48:17','In this tutorial, we will b