ent leaderboards.\n\nYou can tap on the center action button to open up more options.\n<ul>\n	<li>The <strong>+</strong>symbol tobuy shares</li>\n	<li>The <strong>-</strong> button to sell shares</li>\n	<li>The <strong>speech</strong> symbol to post comments. Comments will be sent to your followers and will also appear on your timeline. You are also given options to share your comments on Twitter, Facebook and LinkedIn.</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong style=\"font-size: 1.5em;\">2. Community</strong>\n\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/1community.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-229\" alt=\"1community\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/1community.png\" width=\"318\" height=\"402\" /></a>\n\nFind top traders in the leaderboards, ranked either by raw P&amp;L or by our custom Hero quotient ranking algorithm. You can filter by stock exchange, industry sectors, monthly and quarterly returns and Most Skilled traders.\n\nAlso, you can compete with your friends on the Friends Leaderboard. How so? By connecting accounts from Facebook, Twitter and LinkedInto see how you stack up amongst your friends.\n<h2><strong>3. Portfolio</strong></h2>\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/position.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-232\" alt=\"position\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/position.png\" width=\"320\" height=\"496\" /></a>\n\nThis screen details your current portfolio of stocks: open positions are shown at the top. Closed positions are displayed below. You can tap on the names of stocks to view more details about your positions. Also, you can tap on the right arrows to see the trade history for each position.\n<h2><strong>4. Followers</strong></h2>\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/followers.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-230\" alt=\"followers\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/followers.jpg\" width=\"328\" height=\"482\" /></a>