22 17:40:34','<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/mac2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-439\" alt=\"mac2\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/mac2.jpg\" width=\"750\" height=\"250\" /></a>\r\n\r\nWe are pleased to announce the winners of Macquarie WarrantHero Week 1!\r\n\r\n<em id=\"__mceDel\">\r\nBased on the leader board and the \"3 warrant position*\" requirement, here are the list of winners for Week 1. *To qualify for prizes, users must have at least 3 open or closed positions in the competition participating period.</em>\r\n\r\n<strong>1. SILVERSURFER - S$500\r\n2. KELVIN CHUI - S$300\r\n3. HWEE - S$300\r\n4. BERN VIVALA - S$100\r\n5. DRAGNOR - S$100</strong>\r\n\r\nFor users who have missed out, you are still eligible for 2 more weekly prizes of $1,300 and a $5,000 prize pool for monthly prizes, so keep trading!\r\n<div><strong>Top trader makes 29% last week</strong></div>\r\nWithin just one week of the Warrant Hero launch, trader<strong>SILVERSURFER</strong>has made it to the top of the leader board with a 28.5% gain on his warrant portfolio!\r\n\r\n<strong>Top WarrantHero trader takes positions over Hang Seng and China</strong>\r\nSilversurfer entered his first trade on 12 August  the date the WarrantHero game started  with a buy order for<strong><em>HSI call warrant</em></strong>HSI 21600 MB ECW130927 (SP0W), where the underlying Hang Seng futures made a jump more than 350 points or 1.5%, within half an hour.\r\n\r\nThe spike in the Hang Seng was similar to that seen in the<strong><em>China A50 futures</em></strong>on the same day, where Silversurfer also took a bullish position via FTSECHINAA50 7800 MBECW131030 (S3PW). He exited from both positions the next day with a 58.9% on his HSI warrant, and 30% on his China A50 trade. This compares with the 3.7% gain on the HSI futures and 2.8% increase in the China A50 futures over the same period.\r\n\r\nStill bullish on China, Silversurfer re-entered with the same China A50 call warrant on Wednesday. His view this time round however, was wrong and he quickly cut out of this trade with a 19% loss when the futures fell 1.4%.\r\n\r\n<strong>Runner up focuses on Japan index</strong>\r\nFirst runner-up<strong>KELVIN CHUI</strong>also focused on an index warrant  the Nikkei. He was bearish and bought both the shorter-dated Nikkei put NIKKEI225 13500 MB EPW130913 (S9XW) as well as longer-dated NIKKEI225 12500 MB EPW131213 (ST1W). S9XW and ST1W made him 22.1% and 22.6% respectively. The Nikkei futures fell 2.2% over the same period of time.\r\n\r\n<strong>Open position in HSI puts Hwee in third place</strong>\r\nSecond runner-up<strong>HWEE</strong>traded both a mix of stock and index warrants. In single stocks, he made a 1.5% return in DBS call warrant DBS MB ECW131101 (SB5W) versus DBS 0.7% gain over the same period.\r\n\r\nMost of his gains however, came from an open position in HSI call warrant HSI 25600 MB ECW131230 (RQ5W). He bought the warrant at $0.021 on Monday morning, which gave him a 28.6% unrealised profit based on the warrants closing bid price of $0.027 on Friday.\r\n\r\n<em>Think you can top them? Come on and<a href=\"http://www.tradehero.mobi/warranthero?utm_source=TH&amp;utm_medium=Weeklyemail1&amp;utm_campaign=WarrantHero\" target=\"_self\">join Warrant Hero</a>and stand to win cash prizes. There will be prizes awarded every week for the next 11 weeks! Learn more about warrants from<a href=\"http://www.warrants.com.sg/investoracademy/\" target=\"_self\">Macquarie Investor Academy</a>.</em>\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\n\r\nTradeHero Team\r\n\r\nLike us on Facebook:<a href=\"http://tradehero.us6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=687f1a72d83e850d26ac3aaf6&amp;id=154546d4b5&amp;e=ee084ac939\">www.facebook.com/tradehero</a>\r\nFollow us on Twitter:<a href=\"http://tradehero.us6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=687f1a72d83e850d26ac3aaf6&amp;id=434f3f7a5a&amp;e=ee084ac939\">www.twitter.com/tradeheromobile</a>','Macquarie WarrantHero - Week 1','','inherit','closed','open','','459-revision-4','','','2013-08-23 01:40:34','2013-08-22 17:40:34','',459,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/459-revision-4',0,'revision','',0),(500,4,'2013-09-26 23:19:27','2013-09-26 15:19:27','<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th><a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/mac2.jpg\"><img alt=\"mac2\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/mac2.jpg\" width=\"750\" height=\"250\" /></a>Trader generates return of 140% and takes home monthly prize</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Macquarie is pleased to announce the first monthly winners for the WarrantHero contest, with the leaders taking home cash prizes of up to $2,500 each. The winners of the Warrant Hero contest are decided based on returns generated in a simulated warrant trading environment mirroring the actual live market. Top monthly trader Mr Yau Teng Yan realised trading returns of more than 140 per centin one of his warrants by taking a position in HSI puts as the markets fell. Runners up Rinson Keat and <!--?xml:namespace prefix = \"st1\" ns = \"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" /-->Aaron Bay were also bearish, profiting from jumps in put warrant prices over the past three weeks.<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.warrants.com.sg/home/winners/winners.jpg\" />The top weekly traders from last week were also bearish, generating their returns by buying put warrants over regional indices and local banks. Global markets have been in decline over recent weeks as the US weighs its option over Syria and the future direction for Quantitative Easing (QE) remains uncertain.<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<strong>Top monthly trader make gains in HSI puts</strong>\r\n\r\nTrader Yau Teng Yan was the top performer for the first month of the WarrantHero contest with his biggest gain coming from a position on a Hang Seng (HSI) put warrant. Teng Yan bought the short dated HSI put HSI21600 MBe